The paper deals with index coding problems, which are related to information theory and coding theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the computation of minrank, which involves linear algebra and matrix theory, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) another likely sub-category. The paper also presents a method for reduction of the given minrank computation problem, which involves graph theory and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the construction of index codes, which involves coding theory and combinatorics, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) possible sub-categories.
